OL,3,CMLA pay, Stormont reform, and
OL,4,Cgovernment by social media
OL,6,FThe folks on the hill are set to
OL,7,Freceive a #14,000 pay rise - and not
OL,8,Feveryone is happy about it.
OL,10,FThe Independent Remuneration Panel has
OL,11,Fproposed an uplift in salaries for
OL,12,FMLAs from #53,000 to #67,200 per year
OL,13,F` a rise of 26.8%, from April 1.
OL,15,FPoliticians from across the piece have
OL,16,Fbeen reacting to the proposals.
OL,18,FFirst Minister Michelle O'Neill told
OL,19,Freporters at Stormont that public
OL,20,Fanger about the proposed salary hike
OL,21,Fis "understandable".
OL,26,@}D@DOU}D@SO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/7
